Usage

%*%(x, y)

Arguments

x

An object of class FastTransform, created using fort().

y

A numeric (real) matrix/vector with an appropriate number of rows/elements.

Value

A numeric (real) matrix with the same number of columns as y.

See also

fort() to create FastTransform objects, and %***% for unsafe evaluation
